property.name: text
property.value: This example Models a storage system where jobs arrive at random, are processed by the CPU, which then writes to Disk1, after which the CPU does more processing, writes to Disk2, and finally performs a third batch of CPU processing. The incoming jobs are time stamped with the time of arrival, and upon final departure, the model measures the overall latency of the job. The CPU execution times and disk processing times are exponential random variables, and jobs are queued while those resources are busy.

property.name: text
property.value: This submodel implements a server with a random service time. Upon arrival of an event on any input channel, the ColtExponential actor generates a new random number from an exponential distribution. This random number gives the service time that the newly arrived event will experience when it is served. If the queue is empty, it will be served immediately. Otherwise, it will be serviced when the server has served all events ahead of it in the queue. The average service time is given by a parameter.
